theorem interior_closure_interior_nonempty_iff_nonempty_of_P2
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hP2 : Topology.P2 A) :
    (interior (closure (interior A))).Nonempty ↔ A.Nonempty := by
  classical
  constructor
  · rintro ⟨x, hx⟩
    -- Either `interior A` is non-empty, in which case so is `A`,
    -- or we derive a contradiction from `hx`.
    by_cases hIntA : (interior A).Nonempty
    ·
      rcases hIntA with ⟨y, hy⟩
      exact ⟨y, (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ A) hy⟩
    ·
      -- If `interior A = ∅`, then its closure (and hence the given interior) is empty,
      -- contradicting `hx`.
      have hIntAeq : interior A = (∅ : Set X) := by
        apply Set.eq_empty_iff_forall_not_mem.mpr
        intro y hy
        exact hIntA ⟨y, hy⟩
      have hxCl : x ∈ closure (interior A) :=
        (interior_subset : interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ closure (interior A)) hx
      have : x ∈ (∅ : Set X) := by
        simpa [hIntAeq] using hxCl
      exact (Set.not_mem_empty x) this
  · intro hA
    exact
      Topology.interior_closure_interior_nonempty_of_P2 (A := A) hP2 hA
